Dan WolkenUSA TODAYThe American economic boom of the last decade has gone hand-in-hand with a fundamental change in the financial reach of college athletics.
But the looming economic fallout from the coronavirus pandemic has raised a question that athletic departments of all sizes are scrambling to assess: Is the party over?
Another administrator mentioned potential layoffs or significant cuts if loss of football revenue reached 15% or 20% of the budget.
Just Tuesday, Baylor extended its season ticket renewal period to April 15, and Arkansas moved the deadline for Razorback Foundation pledges by a week to April 6.
